	SerialICE Targets
	SerialICE Targets

SerialICE supports almost any MIPS board as a Target. Each SerialICE
Target needs to be equipped with a suitably configured SerialICE Kernel.
The SerialICE package provides a number of example SerialICE Kernels.
However, it is also quite simple to port
a kernel to any target board that contains a serial port and 
minimal ROM and RAM. This package currently
contains SerialICE Kernel examples for the following boards.

BDMR400x (4001/2/3) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the four flash memories containing the 
	SerialICE Kernel in U8, 
	U19, U29, and U40.
  »  Connect a serial cable from U28 to the 
	SerialICE Controller or Host.

Nitro (4010) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the flash memory containing the 
	SerialICE Kernel in U18.
  »  Connect a serial cable from J18 to the 
	SerialICE Controller or Host.

BDMR4101 (4101) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the four flash memories containing the 
	SerialICE Kernel in U5, 
	U6, U7, and U8.
  »  Connect a serial cable from U27 to the 
	SerialICE Controller or Host.

Nitro II (4011) Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the EPROM memory containing the 
	SerialICE Kernel in U4.
  »  Connect a serial cable from J18 to the 
	SerialICE Controller or Host.

LR4102 TinyRISC Evaluation Board

  »  Insert the EPROM memory containing the 
	SerialICE Kernel in U25.
  »  Connect a serial cable from J9 to the 
	SerialICE Controller or Host.

